b. Feature Selection
Encoding Categorical Variables: Apply one-hot encoding to sex, smoker, and region.

Multicollinearity Check: Calculate Variance Inflation Factor (VIF) to detect multicollinearity.

Feature Importance: Use statistical methods like p-values from regression analysis to determine feature significance.
Medium

c. Model Training
Data Splitting: Divide the dataset into training and testing sets (e.g., 80/20 split).

Model Selection: Use scikit-learn's LinearRegression for model training.

Training: Fit the model on the training data.
Medium

d. Model Evaluation
Performance Metrics:

Mean Absolute Error (MAE)

Mean Squared Error (MSE)

Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)

R-squared (RÂ²)

Residual Analysis: Plot residuals to assess the goodness-of-fit.
